Brayden Travis, 18, was left without medical attention for seven hours after taking drugs at a friend's house in St Charles County, Missouri in early March .
His lungs and kidneys failed, and he suffered a stroke and severe brain damage .
Doctors warned that he would likely remain in a vegetative state, his mother Kelly Smith-Miller shared a photo of him unconscious in a hospital bed with breathing apparatus and wires across his body .
The post has been shared more than 337,000 times on Facebook .